theorem result (p : Position) :
    ∃ k, (((p.nth k).swapped k).1 < k ∧ k < ((p.nth k).swapped k).2) ∨
      (((p.nth k).swapped k).2 < k ∧ k < ((p.nth k).swapped k).1) := by
  by_contra h
  push_neg at h
  let N := 2021
  let edges : Finset (Fin N × Fin N) := Finset.univ.biUnion fun k =>
    let (a, b) := (p.nth k).swapped k
    {(a, k), (b, k)}
  -- Each step k adds exactly 2 edges incident to k. Total edges counted with multiplicity is 2N.
  -- The negation of the goal implies for all k, neighbors a, b are both > k or both < k.
  -- This creates a directed graph where edges are directed a -> k if a > k (k is min) or k -> a if a < k (k is max).
  -- Let S_min be the set of k that are local minimums, S_max local maximums.
  -- Edges always go from S_max u S_min ... actually edges directed by value.
  -- Every k is processed once as a center, creating 2 edges.
  -- If k in S_min, 2 incoming edges (from neighbors).
  -- If k in S_max, 2 outgoing edges (to neighbors).
  -- Also k appears as a neighbor of other centers.
  -- Let d_in(x) and d_out(x) be the total degrees.
  -- Sum d_in = Sum d_out = 2N.
  -- For any x, let n_x be times x is neighbor of a min-center (contributes to d_out of x? No, edge u->x. x is min. u is neighbor. u->x. x gets incoming. u gets outgoing.)
